Crow! Crow!

106
00:06:17,180 --> 00:06:18,310
You're going after the wrong one!
Crow! Crow!

107
00:06:19,440 --> 00:06:20,980
Weren't we lucky we found it?

108
00:06:20,980 --> 00:06:23,230
Yeah, we were. It's all thanks to you.

109
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:25,690
Now you can play with me, right?

110
00:06:26,110 --> 00:06:27,530
What are you after?

111
00:06:27,860 --> 00:06:30,110
Why have you been hanging around me?

112
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:32,910
Like I said, I want to play on the beach.

113
00:06:32,910 --> 00:06:36,330
We can play tag, and splash water on each other.

114
00:06:36,330 --> 00:06:41,460
And, at the end, we'll say, "See you tomorrow!" and part ways.

115
00:06:42,210 --> 00:06:45,000
That sounds like something that friends would do.

116
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:46,420
Yeah. Friends...

117
00:06:46,760 --> 00:06:48,840
You and I are friends.

118
00:06:51,340 --> 00:06:52,390
So...

119
00:06:53,300 --> 00:06:54,680
I want to play!

120
00:06:54,890 --> 00:06:57,140
We don't even know each other's names.

121
00:06:57,140 --> 00:06:59,640
My name is Kamio Misuzu. What's yours?

122
00:07:00,690 --> 00:07:01,900
Kunisaki Yukito...

123
00:07:01,900 --> 00:07:04,440
But listen! I have work to do.

124
00:07:06,690 --> 00:07:09,820
I'm hungry, so I have to earn some money.

125
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:11,570
Oh! If that's the case...

126
00:07:12,950 --> 00:07:16,450
I ended up following her home, lured by the thought of food.

127
00:07:17,120 --> 00:07:19,250
It's nice to eat with someone else, isn't it?

128
00:07:19,540 --> 00:07:21,250
Do you usually eat alone?

129
00:07:21,580 --> 00:07:25,210
My Mom gets home late. And I don't have a Dad.

130
00:07:27,960 --> 00:07:29,840
After you finish eating, let's go play, okay?

131
00:07:29,840 --> 00:07:32,840
No. If it gets late, I'll have trouble finding a place to stay.

132
00:07:33,090 --> 00:07:35,640
You haven't found a place to stay yet?

133
00:07:35,850 --> 00:07:37,890
No. I'll probably end up sleeping outside.

134
00:07:37,890 --> 00:07:39,480
You can stay here!

135
00:07:41,310 --> 00:07:44,190
Now, listen. We just met today.

136
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:46,980
And you have no idea who the heck I am.

137
00:07:46,980 --> 00:07:48,650
I'm a stranger.

138
00:07:48,900 --> 00:07:51,110
Who in their right mind would let someone like that stay the night?

139
00:07:51,400 --> 00:07:53,160
Your mother probably wouldn't allow it anyway.

140
00:07:53,780 --> 00:07:57,950
My Mom's really lax, so I don't think it will be a problem.

141
00:07:57,950 --> 00:08:01,370
Although I guess I shouldn't talk about my mother like that.

142
00:08:01,370 --> 00:08:03,580
But really, it's okay for you to stay here.

143
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:06,670
