268
00:14:52,990 --> 00:14:56,790
Give up, you evil extraterrestrial!

269
00:14:59,410 --> 00:15:00,500
You won't get away!

270
00:15:06,880 --> 00:15:08,380
What are you doing?

271
00:15:13,470 --> 00:15:17,430
A strange extraterrestrial being ran away with my puppet.

272
00:15:18,850 --> 00:15:19,890
You mean this?

273
00:15:20,140 --> 00:15:22,900
Potato isn't an extraterrestrial.

274
00:15:22,980 --> 00:15:25,360
He's a neighborhood stray dog.

275
00:15:25,610 --> 00:15:28,190
You mean, that's really a dog?

276
00:15:29,610 --> 00:15:30,820
I see...

277
00:15:30,820 --> 00:15:31,780
Huh?

278
00:15:35,280 --> 00:15:36,370
I see...

279
00:15:36,580 --> 00:15:39,450
I'm sorry he caused you so much trouble.

280
00:15:39,450 --> 00:15:40,750
Why are you apologizing?

281
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:44,750
Well, Potato said that he brought your puppet here.

282
00:15:44,750 --> 00:15:46,710
It seems he wanted to play with you.

283
00:15:47,050 --> 00:15:49,260
You mean you can understand what he's saying?

284
00:15:49,260 --> 00:15:51,170
Yes! We're best friends.

285
00:15:51,430 --> 00:15:52,630
Right, Potato?

286
00:15:53,890 --> 00:15:58,140
It seems that there are still worlds here on Earth that I know nothing about.

287
00:16:00,020 --> 00:16:00,890
Thanks.

288
00:16:02,190 --> 00:16:04,060
Are you hurt or something?

289
00:16:04,060 --> 00:16:04,860
Oh, this?

290
00:16:05,270 --> 00:16:07,360
Well, uh...

291
00:16:08,110 --> 00:16:10,150
Nope! I have to keep it a secret.

292
00:16:13,950 --> 00:16:16,620
My name is Kirishima Kano. What's your name?

293
00:16:16,620 --> 00:16:17,950
I'm Kunisaki Yukito.

294
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:20,250
Do you have some free time, by any chance?

295
00:16:20,250 --> 00:16:21,040
I guess...

296
00:16:21,040 --> 00:16:25,380
Okay! Then you will be Citizen Number 2 of Planet Dilly-Dally.

297
00:16:25,380 --> 00:16:26,710
Who's Number 1?

298
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:31,010
Me! And Potato is Number 3.

299
00:16:32,470 --> 00:16:34,890
And what do the citizens of Planet Dilly-Dally do?

300
00:16:35,180 --> 00:16:36,720
They just have time on their hands.

301
00:16:37,010 --> 00:16:39,680
That is the fate of those from Planet Dilly-Dally.

302
00:16:39,680 --> 00:16:41,560
Right? We have nothing to do, do we, Potato?

303
00:16:44,600 --> 00:16:48,400
I have to go to school, so I'll say good-bye for now.

304
00:16:48,940 --> 00:16:50,730
I thought you were from Planet Dilly-Dally?

305
00:16:50,980 --> 00:16:54,570
You believed that? You're such a kid!

306
00:16:55,700 --> 00:16:56,620
So long!

307
00:16:57,620 --> 00:17:01,160
Are all the girls who wear that uniform weird?

308
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:02,910
Hey!

309
00:17:04,750 --> 00:17:05,710
What is it?

310
00:17:05,710 --> 00:17:09,380
Have you ever wished you could do magic?

311
00:17:11,460 --> 00:17:12,510
What?

312
00:17:14,470 --> 00:17:16,890
You're stunned! So long!

313
00:17:18,510 --> 00:17:19,510
Magic?

314
00:17:28,810 --> 00:17:31,360
Oh, Yukito-san!

315
00:17:31,360 --> 00:17:33,320
How did your work go?

316
00:17:33,740 --> 00:17:35,700
I made a mint.

317
00:17:36,950 --> 00:17:37,990
Really?

318
00:17:38,320 --> 00:17:40,030
I'm sorry. I lied.

319
00:17:41,030 --> 00:17:44,410
I have to find someplace where there are more people or I won't be able to make a living.

320
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:48,830
Why is this place so quiet when people should be returning from work?

321
00:17:49,040 --> 00:17:52,130
Well, this station is closed down.

322
00:17:52,130 --> 00:17:53,840
You should have told me that earlier.

323
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:55,420
G-gao!

324
00:17:56,260 --> 00:17:57,010
Ouch!

325
00:17:57,340 --> 00:17:59,510
Why'd you hit me?

326
00:18:00,350 --> 00:18:05,100
Haruko told me to scold you whenever you say that.

327
00:18:05,390 --> 00:18:07,520
Oh! How cute!

328
00:18:12,940 --> 00:18:14,400
It's Tohno-san...

329
00:18:15,110 --> 00:18:16,490
You know her?

330
00:18:16,490 --> 00:18:17,400
Yeah.

331
00:18:20,450 --> 00:18:22,240
Why are you getting so anxious?

332
00:18:23,160 --> 00:18:26,000
H-hello!

333
00:18:27,910 --> 00:18:30,580
Hello. This is unexpected.

334
00:18:30,580 --> 00:18:34,050
Y-yes. Quite a coincidence.

335
00:18:34,630 --> 00:18:35,340
I'm astonished.

336
00:18:37,550 --> 00:18:39,010
What were you doing?

337
00:18:39,380 --> 00:18:41,220
Getting some sun.

338
00:18:42,430 --> 00:18:45,600
Just kidding. It's evening right now.

339
00:18:46,850 --> 00:18:48,600
Hey, who the heck is this girl?

340
00:18:48,600 --> 00:18:51,860
It's Tohno Minagi-san. She's my classmate.

341
00:18:51,860 --> 00:18:56,070
She's smart. She's at the top of our grade, and she's president of the Astronomy Club.

342
00:18:56,900 --> 00:19:00,990
Please just call me Tohno.

343
00:19:00,990 --> 00:19:03,580
Hey! Minagi!

344
00:19:08,870 --> 00:19:12,580
Oh, Yukito-san is flying like a leaf!

345
00:19:13,210 --> 00:19:16,000
Hey, hey! Let's hurry up and go back to blowing bubbles!

346
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:18,550
I'm doing really good now, you know!

347
00:19:18,550 --> 00:19:18,880
Please!

348
00:19:19,220 --> 00:19:21,890
Is this girl your little sister?

349
00:19:21,890 --> 00:19:25,390
No, I'm not. I'm Michiru, Minagi's best friend.

350
00:19:25,390 --> 00:19:26,930
And who could you be?

351
00:19:26,930 --> 00:19:29,310
I'm Tohno-san's classmate.

352
00:19:29,310 --> 00:19:31,900
That hurt, you know.

353
00:19:32,060 --> 00:19:34,860
What?! Are you another one of Minagi's classmates?

354
00:19:35,110 --> 00:19:38,320
I'm an innocent passerby who got bowled over by you.

355
00:19:42,070 --> 00:19:46,530
